Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Notice of Expert Testimony, filed.

Defendant Lemont R Siller not in court, in custody.  Attorney Carl Bradford Johnson appeared by video for Lemont R Siller.  Attorney Jacob Daniel Corr in court for State of Wisconsin. Case set requests Final Pretrial and Jury Trial dates. Any witness lists, special jury instructions, and motion in limine to be filed by the final pretrial date. Any other motions and notice of alibi must be filed by the final pretrial. Court orders case adjourned for final pretrial and jury trial in Branch 4.
Final pre-trial scheduled for November 11, 2022 at 03:00 pm.
Jury trial scheduled for January 3, 2023 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Lemont R Siller not in court, in custody.  Attorney Carl Bradford Johnson appeared by video for Lemont R Siller.  Attorney Jacob Daniel Corr in court for State of Wisconsin. State advised the Court they have complied with the Victims' Rights Law. Arguments heard as to bail. Court orders bail to $100,000.00 cash bail with all other previously ordered conditions of bail.
Petition for Review of Bail.

Defendant Lemont R Siller in court (via zoom) with attorney Carl Bradford Johnson (in person). Defendant Lemont R Siller in custody.   Jacob Daniel Corr appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Case in court to address state's joinder motion. Defense takes no position on joinder. Court grants joinder of co-actor case 2022CF2389 (Jackson-Milton). Defense makes oral bail motion due to possible extension of speedy trial demand.  Court finds good cause for extension of speedy trial demand. Court further advises unable to address bail due to victim's rights. Parties to file bail motion for victim notification. Discussions of further handling of discovery and co-actors placed on the record. Parties in agreement of status hearing. Case adjourned in Branch 4.

Attorney Carl Bradford Johnson in court, defendant Lemont R Siller not in court, in custody.  Chad Wozniak appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case in court for final pre-trial. State advised Court of newly charged co-actor and requested Joinder. Court aware of possible Joinder however will hear at next hearing with all co-defendants.  Jury trial date remains calendared at this time. Case adjourned to Br 4.  Motion hearing scheduled for August 17, 2022 at 04:00 pm.
State's Motion to Join Cases for Trial.
Defendant's Motion in Limine, received and filed.

Any other motions must be filed by the final pretrial.  Court orders case adjourned for final pretrial and jury trial in Branch 4.  Final pre-trial scheduled for August 2, 2022 at 09:00 am.  Jury trial scheduled for August 22, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Defendant enters a SPEEDY TRIAL DEMAND. Exp. 8/24/2022

Defendant Lemont R Siller in court with attorney Carl Bradford Johnson.  Defendant Lemont R Siller in custody.  Jacob Daniel Corr appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Lemont R Siller appeared by video means with Attorney.
Die to the pending co-defendant matter, this case is re-assigned to Br. 4. Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: Detective Elizabeth Rubio.   State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 4.  Scheduling conference scheduled for June 13, 2022 at 08:30 am.
